📚 Kubernetes Storage Notes (PV, PVC, Dynamic Volume Provisioning)
1️⃣ Persistent Volume (PV)

Persistent Volume (PV) is the actual storage resource in the Kubernetes cluster.

In Amazon EKS, the storage is usually backed by AWS EBS volumes.

PV is generally created and managed by the cluster or through a StorageClass.

Example PV YAML

apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolume
metadata:
  name: my-pv
spec:
  capacity:
    storage: 1Gi
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteOnce
  storageClassName: ebs-storage

Check PV

kubectl get pv
2️⃣ Persistent Volume Claim (PVC)

Persistent Volume Claim (PVC) is a request for storage made by a Pod.

A Pod does not use PV directly.

Flow:

Pod → PVC → PV → Storage

Example PVC YAML

apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: my-pvc
spec:
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteOnce
  storageClassName: ebs-storage
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: 1Gi

Create PVC

kubectl apply -f pvc.yml

Check PVC

kubectl get pvc
3️⃣ Dynamic Volume Provisioning

Normally:

Admin → PV create
User → PVC create

But with Dynamic Provisioning, Kubernetes automatically creates a PV when a PVC is created.

This works through a StorageClass.

Example StorageClass

apiVersion: storage.k8s.io/v1
kind: StorageClass
metadata:
  name: ebs-storage
provisioner: ebs.csi.aws.com
volumeBindingMode: WaitForFirstConsumer
reclaimPolicy: Delete

Create StorageClass

kubectl apply -f sc.yml

Check StorageClass

kubectl get sc
4️⃣ volumeBindingMode
Immediate
volumeBindingMode: Immediate

The volume is created immediately when the PVC is created.

Flow:

PVC Created
   ↓
PV Created Immediately
WaitForFirstConsumer
volumeBindingMode: WaitForFirstConsumer

The volume is created only when a Pod using the PVC is scheduled.

Flow:

PVC Created
   ↓
Pod Scheduled
   ↓
PV Created

Benefit:

Helps Kubernetes choose the correct node before creating the volume.

5️⃣ reclaimPolicy
Delete
reclaimPolicy: Delete

Flow:

PVC Deleted
   ↓
PV Deleted
   ↓
Storage Deleted

Use Case:

Temporary environments

Testing workloads

Retain
reclaimPolicy: Retain

Flow:

PVC Deleted
   ↓
PV Remains
   ↓
Storage Remains

Meaning:

The storage and data are not deleted

Manual cleanup is required

Use Case:

Databases

Important production data

6️⃣ StatefulSet Behavior

In StatefulSet, pods are created and deleted sequentially (one by one).

Example pod order:

pod-0
pod-1
pod-2

If a pod is deleted:

kubectl delete pod pod-1

Kubernetes recreates it with the same identity and storage.

Check pods:

kubectl get pods
7️⃣ Important Kubernetes Commands
Check Storage Resources
kubectl get pv
kubectl get pvc
kubectl get sc
Describe Resources
kubectl describe pv
kubectl describe pvc
🗑️ Delete Commands
Delete All PVC
kubectl delete pvc --all
Delete All PV
kubectl delete pv --all
Delete All Pods
kubectl delete pods --all
Delete Specific Pod
kubectl delete pod pod-name
📌 Short Summary
Component	Meaning
PV	Actual storage
PVC	Storage request
StorageClass	Defines storage configuration
Dynamic Provisioning	Automatic PV creation
Delete Policy	Storage deleted
Retain Policy	Storage and data preserved
